Repost from @thetravelmom

Mālama means to take care of, tend, attend, care for, preserve, protect. Watch this great video explaining what it means for the Islands of Hawaii and how YOU can help. This is such an important concept for all of us, no matter where we live. Feel free to share it so hopefully we can inspire others. @gohawaii @hawaiianairlines @hiltonhawaiianvillage @hiltonhotels @oahuvb @gunstockranch @hawaiinewsnow

node.text:
After this last year and a half, I appreciate even more the opportunity to get up and go somewhere. So visiting this beautiful masterpiece of a destination was such a gift. Hawaii gives so much of “herself” through her ecosystem and more and so we are thankful that she let us spend some time with her. Part one of our journey to Hawaii and the island of Oahu airs this Sunday at 3:30 on @abc7newsbayarea.  @hiltonhawaiianvillage @visit.hawaii @visitoahu @hotspotsurfschool @yumisupyoga @kualoaranch @bishopmuseum @giovannisshrimptruck @tihatiproductions #hawaii #oahu #travelingwithkids #julesmom #dayswithzahrah #travelingduringcovid #aloha #surfingmom @gunstockranch @naturamortaphotography @khamisi

node.text:
Had the most stunning breakfast at Bali Oceanfront at @hiltonhawaiianvillage today 😍🏝 It felt like our own little mini staycation! 

We ordered: 
🥑 Bravocado Toast with 63 Degree Egg 
🥘 Kiawe Brisket Huevos Rancheros 
🍳 Paniolo Omelette 
🍲 Bali Breakfast Bowl 
🥂 Mimosas
🍪 Chocolate Muffin 

My order was the avo toast, which I got with tomato olive feta (you could also choose salmon cream cheese). I liked the generous amount of avocado and feta crumbles. The 63 degree egg is basically like an onsen egg! It all went together perfectly with a cup of English Breakfast tea and a mimosa (virgin for me, lilikoi for @stkuroda). And pro-tip: DON’T MISS OUT ON THAT CHOCOLATE MUFFIN. It had a generous amount of chocolate chips and was really moist – basically an excuse to eat chocolate cake for breakfast 🙃
@kanakattackks 
Thank you @hiltonhawaiianvillage and @hawaiifoodieclub for having us! ☀️
